and talk about what

00:00:39.730 --> 00:00:42.270 align:middle line:84%
to do when life throws
you curve balls,

00:00:42.270 --> 00:00:45.300 align:middle line:84%
and how to overcome
those obstacles.

00:00:45.300 --> 00:00:47.770 align:middle line:84%
Lisa is known as the
breakthrough specialist,

00:00:47.770 --> 00:00:50.550 align:middle line:84%
and she has an enormous
amount of breakthroughs

00:00:50.550 --> 00:00:53.980 align:middle line:84%
that she has had in her life
and a lot of breakdowns, too.

00:00:53.980 --> 00:00:54.500 align:middle line:90%
You have?

00:00:54.500 --> 00:00:55.584 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the show, Lisa.

00:00:55.584 --> 00:00:57.249 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA NICHOLS: Thank
you so much, Lisa.

00:00:57.249 --> 00:00:59.850 align:middle line:84%
I'm so excited to be here with
you and to be in your space

00:00:59.850 --> 00:01:00.500 align:middle line:90%
again.

00:01:00.500 --> 00:01:02.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It is my honor
because I love you.

00:01:02.980 --> 00:01:04.879 align:middle line:90%
I think you are fabulous.

00:01:04.879 --> 00:01:06.857 align:middle line:84%
And you came from
not far around here.

00:01:06.857 --> 00:01:08.190 align:middle line:90%
You grew up in this area, right?

00:01:08.190 --> 00:01:10.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: No, this is
my old neighborhood.

00:01:10.190 --> 00:01:14.050 align:middle line:84%
We had a lot of fun, did a lot
of damage over in this area.

00:01:14.050 --> 00:01:15.850 align:middle line:90%
So I'm glad to be here with you.

00:01:15.850 --> 00:01:20.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I always hear you talk
about your story and where I

00:01:20.060 --> 00:01:22.596 align:middle line:84%
see you now is this
magnificent speaker and--

00:01:22.596 --> 00:01:23.470 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Thank you.

00:01:23.470 --> 00:01:25.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: --such an
inspiration to so many people,

00:01:25.010 --> 00:01:26.724 align:middle line:84%
but it wasn't
always like for you.

00:01:26.724 --> 00:01:27.640 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Not at all.

00:01:27.640 --> 00:01:29.960 align:middle line:84%
I think that my life
represents-- and I

00:01:29.960 --> 00:01:32.150 align:middle line:84%
hear from all over
the world whenever

00:01:32.150 --> 00:01:35.350 align:middle line:84%
I travel internationally,
people always

00:01:35.350 --> 00:01:37.340 align:middle line:90%
say you remind me of myself.

00:01:37.340 --> 00:01:41.890 align:middle line:84%
And I think I'm the people's
person, the people's inspirator

00:01:41.890 --> 00:01:44.620 align:middle line:84%
because I represent
getting back up.

00:01:44.620 --> 00:01:47.710 align:middle line:84%
My life is a result
of being committed

00:01:47.710 --> 00:01:50.360 align:middle line:90%
to get back up one more time.

00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:51.800 align:middle line:84%
Not counting the
number times I've

00:01:51.800 --> 00:01:54.350 align:middle line:84%
been knocked down,
not singing that song,

00:01:54.350 --> 00:01:57.080 align:middle line:84%
being committed to get
back up one more time.

00:01:57.080 --> 00:01:58.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, that's interesting.

00:01:58.580 --> 00:02:00.680 align:middle line:84%
So you're not so
focused on the times

00:02:00.680 --> 00:02:01.956 align:middle line:90%
where you were knocked down.

00:02:01.956 --> 00:02:03.580 align:middle line:84%
You're focused on
the times you got up.

00:02:03.580 --> 00:02:04.530 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yeah.

00:02:04.530 --> 00:02:07.270 align:middle line:84%
If you notice the stories
that we use to bond

00:02:07.270 --> 00:02:09.300 align:middle line:84%
normally are the stories
of being knocked down.

00:02:09.300 --> 00:02:10.796 align:middle line:90%
Oh, you think that was bad?

00:02:10.796 --> 00:02:12.296 align:middle line:84%
Let me tell you
what happened to me.

00:02:12.296 --> 00:02:15.055 align:middle line:84%
But what if we were bold
enough to celebrate,

00:02:15.055 --> 00:02:17.070 align:middle line:90%
I got up from that?

00:02:17.070 --> 00:02:20.800 align:middle line:84%
Instead of the stripes
of challenges and woes,

00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:22.690 align:middle line:84%
what if there were
badges of get up?

00:02:22.690 --> 00:02:25.614 align:middle line:84%
I got up from being born and
raised in South Central Los

00:02:25.614 --> 00:02:27.280 align:middle line:84%
Angeles and living
between the hollering

00:02:27.280 --> 00:02:28.530 align:middle line:90%
'30s and the rolling '60s.

00:02:28.530 --> 00:02:31.475 align:middle line:84%
I got up from being a C
student and struggling all

00:02:31.475 --> 00:02:32.100 align:middle line:90%
through school.

00:02:32.100 --> 00:02:35.660 align:middle line:84%
I got up from being
touched inappropriately.

00:02:35.660 --> 00:02:36.890 align:middle line:90%
I got up from those things.

00:02:36.890 --> 00:02:38.920 align:middle line:90%
Not that woe, is me.

00:02:38.920 --> 00:02:40.470 align:middle line:90%
I got up from those things.

00:02:40.470 --> 00:02:41.990 align:middle line:90%
So who am I designed to be?

00:02:41.990 --> 00:02:45.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you told me earlier
that you got a D in Speech.

00:02:45.590 --> 00:02:47.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: I got a
D minus in Speech.

00:02:47.470 --> 00:02:48.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How is that possible?

00:02:48.090 --> 00:02:50.423 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Well, not only did
I get a D minus in Speech.

00:02:50.423 --> 00:02:53.600 align:middle line:84%
My Speech teacher said
quote unquote Ms. Nichols,

00:02:53.600 --> 00:02:56.680 align:middle line:84%
I recommend you never
speak in public,

00:02:56.680 --> 00:02:58.100 align:middle line:90%
that you get a desk job.

00:02:58.100 --> 00:02:59.600 align:middle line:90%
And guess what I did.

00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:01.260 align:middle line:90%
I went and got a desk job.

00:03:01.260 --> 00:03:04.840 align:middle line:84%
I was in accounting for seven
years, Lisa, accounting.

00:03:04.840 --> 00:03:05.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Were you really?

00:03:05.840 --> 00:03:06.714 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Oh my God.

00:03:06.714 --> 00:03:08.410 align:middle line:84%
I was such a danger
to the field.

00:03:08.410 --> 00:03:10.790 align:middle line:90%
I was a danger to the field.

00:03:10.790 --> 00:03:11.660 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:03:11.660 --> 00:03:14.782 align:middle line:84%
And I learned there that if
you don't balance by a nickel,

00:03:14.782 --> 00:03:16.240 align:middle line:84%
you have to stay
until you balance.

00:03:16.240 --> 00:03:16.950 align:middle line:90%
Well, I didn't.

00:03:16.950 --> 00:03:18.400 align:middle line:84%
I just pulled a nickel
out from my pocket,

00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:20.100 align:middle line:84%
put it in the drawer,
and went home.

00:03:20.100 --> 00:03:22.022 align:middle line:84%
Someone got in trouble
after four years

00:03:22.022 --> 00:03:24.480 align:middle line:84%
of me being in that industry,
and then I went on three more

00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:29.087 align:middle line:84%
before-- the last job I had,
they brought me in the office.

00:03:29.087 --> 00:03:31.670 align:middle line:84%
And they started reviewing me,
and I got nervous at one point.

00:03:31.670 --> 00:03:33.580 align:middle line:90%
I said are you firing me?

00:03:33.580 --> 00:03:36.600 align:middle line:84%
And they said you're
a really nice lady.

00:03:36.600 --> 00:03:38.190 align:middle line:90%
Everyone here loves you.

00:03:38.190 --> 00:03:39.660 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to
fire you, but we

00:03:39.660 --> 00:03:41.930 align:middle line:84%
do need to release you
to find your dream.

00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:43.130 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:03:43.130 --> 00:03:45.920 align:middle line:84%
I said does that mean I show
up here tomorrow to find it?

00:03:45.920 --> 00:03:48.040 align:middle line:90%
Am I going to look for it here?

00:03:48.040 --> 00:03:50.880 align:middle line:84%
But get this--
fast-forward 20 years,

00:03:50.880 --> 00:03:53.212 align:middle line:84%
I'm standing on stage
in front of 3,000 women.

00:03:53.212 --> 00:03:54.920 align:middle line:84%
And a woman's on the
front row, and she's

00:03:54.920 --> 00:03:55.957 align:middle line:90%
crying the entire time.

00:03:55.957 --> 00:03:58.165 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of the speech,
I finally go up to her,

00:03:58.165 --> 00:04:00.440 align:middle line:84%
and I got you've been crying
for an hour and a half.

00:04:00.440 --> 00:04:01.500 align:middle line:90%
Why are you crying?

00:04:01.500 --> 00:04:04.075 align:middle line:84%
She goes because 20
years ago, I released

00:04:04.075 --> 00:04:07.340 align:middle line:84%
you to find your dream,
and you found it.

00:04:07.340 --> 00:04:09.860 align:middle line:84%
The same woman that
fired me from accounting.

00:04:09.860 --> 00:04:11.810 align:middle line:90%
She goes congratulations.

00:04:11.810 --> 00:04:13.040 align:middle line:90%
You never know.

00:04:13.040 --> 00:04:14.760 align:middle line:90%
Just keep getting back up.

00:04:14.760 --> 00:04:15.320 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:04:15.320 --> 00:04:16.600 align:middle line:84%
You have done that
so many times.

00:04:16.600 --> 00:04:17.990 align:middle line:84%
And the way that
you speak, I mean,

00:04:17.990 --> 00:04:20.089 align:middle line:84%
you would think that you'd
done it all your life.

00:04:20.089 --> 00:04:22.060 align:middle line:84%
The way you touch,
and move, and inspire,

00:04:22.060 --> 00:04:25.280 align:middle line:84%
and the responsiveness
you get from your audience

00:04:25.280 --> 00:04:26.819 align:middle line:90%
is so pure and so beautiful.

00:04:26.819 --> 00:04:28.360 align:middle line:84%
I've got to get
through one interview

00:04:28.360 --> 00:04:29.360 align:middle line:90%
without crying with you.

00:04:29.360 --> 00:04:30.350 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do this.

00:04:30.350 --> 00:04:31.254 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Good luck.

00:04:31.254 --> 00:04:33.062 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:04:33.062 --> 00:04:34.420 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Exactly.

00:04:34.420 --> 00:04:35.680 align:middle line:90%
Because you are so real.

00:04:35.680 --> 00:04:38.530 align:middle line:84%
So you grew up here
in Los Angeles.

00:04:38.530 --> 00:04:41.890 align:middle line:84%
You were a single mom
and raised your child.

00:04:41.890 --> 00:04:44.664 align:middle line:84%
And you made a commitment at
a certain point in your life

00:04:44.664 --> 00:04:46.330 align:middle line:84%
that you were going
to turn this around.

00:04:46.330 --> 00:04:49.760 align:middle line:84%
What was that moment for
you, or series of moments?

00:04:49.760 --> 00:04:51.440 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yeah.

00:04:51.440 --> 00:04:56.040 align:middle line:84%
My son and I lived in Inglewood,
California by the airport.

00:04:56.040 --> 00:04:59.270 align:middle line:84%
And when he was born, I had to
get on government's assistance

00:04:59.270 --> 00:05:00.650 align:middle line:90%
just to have him.

00:05:00.650 --> 00:05:03.460 align:middle line:84%
I didn't have money
to have my baby.

00:05:03.460 --> 00:05:05.570 align:middle line:84%
I didn't have money
to feed my baby.

00:05:05.570 --> 00:05:10.650 align:middle line:84%
And it was a rock bottom, but
it felt like I sunk even lower

00:05:10.650 --> 00:05:14.400 align:middle line:84%
when he was eight months
old, and I didn't have money

00:05:14.400 --> 00:05:16.170 align:middle line:90%
to buy him Pampers.

00:05:16.170 --> 00:05:18.120 align:middle line:84%
And I had to wrap
my son, Jaylani,

00:05:18.120 --> 00:05:21.140 align:middle line:90%
in a towel for two days.

00:05:21.140 --> 00:05:26.930 align:middle line:84%
And I remember my son lying
on the couch on his back.

00:05:26.930 --> 00:05:30.940 align:middle line:84%
Touching his stomach, I
said don't worry, Jaylani.

00:05:30.940 --> 00:05:34.240 align:middle line:84%
Mommy will never be
this broke again.

00:05:34.240 --> 00:05:40.030 align:middle line:84%
And I felt like I felt the
wall of what bottom felt like.

00:05:40.030 --> 00:05:41.560 align:middle line:90%
And I thought OK.

00:05:41.560 --> 00:05:43.260 align:middle line:90%
Now I know what it feels like.

00:05:43.260 --> 00:05:45.010 align:middle line:90%
So now let's get up.

00:05:45.010 --> 00:05:48.290 align:middle line:84%
And I began to-- now,
here's the key thing--

00:05:48.290 --> 00:05:51.770 align:middle line:84%
I began to be comfortable
being uncomfortable

00:05:51.770 --> 00:05:53.340 align:middle line:90%
in a new possibility.

00:05:53.340 --> 00:05:54.440 align:middle line:90%
And I'll say it like this.

00:05:54.440 --> 00:05:59.490 align:middle line:84%
Most people will stay in a
familiar, keyword, familiar

00:05:59.490 --> 00:06:02.890 align:middle line:84%
discomfort, Lisa, before
they're willing to move

00:06:02.890 --> 00:06:06.560 align:middle line:90%
to an unfamiliar possibility.

00:06:06.560 --> 00:06:08.706 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we'll stay in
a place of discomfort--

00:06:08.706 --> 00:06:10.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Because
it's familiar,

00:06:10.080 --> 00:06:11.950 align:middle line:84%
because it's
familiar, versus going

00:06:11.950 --> 00:06:13.940 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what I
don't know is out there,

00:06:13.940 --> 00:06:16.090 align:middle line:90%
but I'm willing to go for it.

00:06:16.090 --> 00:06:19.000 align:middle line:84%
I went and I learned from
people who didn't look like me.

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:21.990 align:middle line:84%
I learned from older
white men who I had never

00:06:21.990 --> 00:06:24.490 align:middle line:84%
had any relationship with
other than my last teacher who

00:06:24.490 --> 00:06:27.264 align:middle line:84%
gave me a fail, a
D minus in Speech.

00:06:27.264 --> 00:06:28.680 align:middle line:84%
I went and learned
from people who

00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:31.520 align:middle line:84%
were genius in particular areas
that I wanted to know about.

00:06:31.520 --> 00:06:32.930 align:middle line:84%
I went to conferences
where I was

00:06:32.930 --> 00:06:36.100 align:middle line:84%
the only woman, the
only person of color.

00:06:36.100 --> 00:06:37.480 align:middle line:90%
I went hungry.

00:06:37.480 --> 00:06:39.640 align:middle line:90%
I went as a hungry student.

00:06:39.640 --> 00:06:40.930 align:middle line:90%
I went knowing nothing.

00:06:40.930 --> 00:06:43.110 align:middle line:84%
With all the brilliance
you might have,

00:06:43.110 --> 00:06:45.020 align:middle line:90%
are you willing to know nothing?

00:06:45.020 --> 00:06:47.840 align:middle line:84%
I was willing to know
nothing for my future.

00:06:47.840 --> 00:06:48.770 align:middle line:90%
I was hungry.

00:06:48.770 --> 00:06:51.320 align:middle line:84%
I was hungry for
rescuing myself.

00:06:51.320 --> 00:06:53.710 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Didn't you step into
the environment and wonder

00:06:53.710 --> 00:06:54.960 align:middle line:90%
are you going to mess this up?

00:06:54.960 --> 00:06:56.120 align:middle line:84%
Am I going to be
looked at as weird?

00:06:56.120 --> 00:06:57.536 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Absolutely,
absolutely.

00:06:57.536 --> 00:06:59.500 align:middle line:84%
I didn't say my knees
weren't knocking

00:06:59.500 --> 00:07:01.179 align:middle line:90%
and my teeth weren't chattering.

00:07:01.179 --> 00:07:02.970 align:middle line:84%
See, a lot of people
wait until they're not

00:07:02.970 --> 00:07:04.289 align:middle line:90%
scared anymore to move.

00:07:04.289 --> 00:07:05.830 align:middle line:84%
I'm willing to leap
while I'm scared.

00:07:05.830 --> 00:07:07.954 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, that's kind
of too late in that point

00:07:07.954 --> 00:07:09.429 align:middle line:84%
because, yeah, the
damage is done.

00:07:09.429 --> 00:07:10.220 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Exactly.

00:07:10.220 --> 00:07:12.230 align:middle line:84%
The opportunity
has passed you by.

00:07:12.230 --> 00:07:13.540 align:middle line:90%
I was scared.

00:07:13.540 --> 00:07:14.850 align:middle line:90%
I was scared.

00:07:14.850 --> 00:07:17.230 align:middle line:84%
When I decided I wanted to
be an inspirational speaker,

00:07:17.230 --> 00:07:18.720 align:middle line:90%
all this chatter kicked in.

00:07:18.720 --> 00:07:20.710 align:middle line:84%
And I still know
the chatter today.

00:07:20.710 --> 00:07:22.729 align:middle line:84%
The chatter was you're
an African American woman

00:07:22.729 --> 00:07:23.520 align:middle line:90%
from South Central.

00:07:23.520 --> 00:07:24.890 align:middle line:90%
Who's going to listen to you?

00:07:24.890 --> 00:07:26.420 align:middle line:84%
The chatter was
you have no money.

00:07:26.420 --> 00:07:26.830 align:middle line:90%
You're broke.

00:07:26.830 --> 00:07:28.663 align:middle line:84%
How are you going to
talk about being happy?

00:07:28.663 --> 00:07:30.724 align:middle line:84%
The chatter was
you're overweight.

00:07:30.724 --> 00:07:33.140 align:middle line:84%
You can't inspire people until
you've managed your weight.

00:07:33.140 --> 00:07:34.040 align:middle line:90%
Well, listen, let me tell you.

00:07:34.040 --> 00:07:36.581 align:middle line:84%
If I waited until I was at my
ideal weight to inspire people,

00:07:36.581 --> 00:07:39.552 align:middle line:84%
you still would not
be hearing my voice.

00:07:39.552 --> 00:07:41.135 align:middle line:84%
You would've missed
out on everything.

00:07:41.135 --> 00:07:42.247 align:middle line:90%
Lisa who?

00:07:42.247 --> 00:07:43.101 align:middle line:90%
Lisa Garr.

00:07:43.101 --> 00:07:43.970 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:07:43.970 --> 00:07:45.450 align:middle line:90%
There would be no Lisa Nichols.

00:07:45.450 --> 00:07:47.440 align:middle line:90%
And so I was willing.

00:07:47.440 --> 00:07:49.750 align:middle line:84%
I was willing, Lisa,
to leap while I

00:07:49.750 --> 00:07:51.395 align:middle line:90%
learned how to get it right.

00:07:51.395 --> 00:07:52.830 align:middle line:90%
Like I'm going to leap, God.

00:07:52.830 --> 00:07:56.010 align:middle line:84%
And then show me quite how to
flap my wings on my way down.

00:07:56.010 --> 00:07:57.990 align:middle line:84%
And if I don't soar,
would you please give me

00:07:57.990 --> 00:07:59.394 align:middle line:90%
something soft to land on?

00:07:59.394 --> 00:08:01.060 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm going to
run and leap again.

00:08:01.060 --> 00:08:04.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I hear you talk
about God a lot in your life.

00:08:04.770 --> 00:08:07.860 align:middle line:84%
Have you had a certain religion
that you've believed in?

00:08:07.860 --> 00:08:09.280 align:middle line:90%
Or is life your religion?

00:08:09.280 --> 00:08:13.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: No, I grew up Baptist
