00:30:02.140 --> 00:30:04.280 align:middle line:84%
I ask him this same
question every six months.

00:30:04.280 --> 00:30:05.227 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, wow.

00:30:05.227 --> 00:30:06.185 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: He's now 18.

00:30:06.185 --> 00:30:08.990 align:middle line:84%
I've asked him every six months
since he was eight years old.

00:30:08.990 --> 00:30:10.670 align:middle line:84%
It drives him crazy
now, by the way.

00:30:10.670 --> 00:30:14.030 align:middle line:84%
I go, Jaylani, on a scale from
1 to-- He goes Mom, really?

00:30:14.030 --> 00:30:14.672 align:middle line:90%
I go really.

00:30:14.672 --> 00:30:16.130 align:middle line:84%
He goes why do you
keep doing this?

00:30:16.130 --> 00:30:18.250 align:middle line:84%
I say because it's my job to
keep checking in with this

00:30:18.250 --> 00:30:19.791 align:middle line:84%
to make sure that
I'm doing the work.

00:30:19.791 --> 00:30:21.940 align:middle line:84%
So the second question is,
after they've rated it,

00:30:21.940 --> 00:30:23.450 align:middle line:84%
first time Jaylani--
I asked him.

00:30:23.450 --> 00:30:25.830 align:middle line:90%
He said a seven, seven.

00:30:25.830 --> 00:30:28.040 align:middle line:84%
It was sobering, like
a ton of bricks hit me.

00:30:28.040 --> 00:30:30.710 align:middle line:84%
But you can't be emotional,
and you can't respond emotional

00:30:30.710 --> 00:30:32.410 align:middle line:84%
because then they're afraid
to tell you the truth again.

00:30:32.410 --> 00:30:33.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:30:33.270 --> 00:30:34.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Then they're
afraid to tell you

00:30:34.130 --> 00:30:34.780 align:middle line:84%
because they don't
want to hurt you.

00:30:34.780 --> 00:30:35.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Sure.

00:30:35.240 --> 00:30:36.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: So when
he said a seven,

00:30:36.120 --> 00:30:37.900 align:middle line:84%
the second question
is the key question.

00:30:37.900 --> 00:30:40.680 align:middle line:84%
What will take it
from a 7 to a 10?

00:30:40.680 --> 00:30:42.327 align:middle line:84%
What will take it
from a 7 to a 10?

00:30:42.327 --> 00:30:44.160 align:middle line:84%
I learned that from my
friend Jack Canfield.

00:30:44.160 --> 00:30:45.060 align:middle line:84%
And I've been doing
it ever since.

00:30:45.060 --> 00:30:47.850 align:middle line:84%
And when I asked my son Jaylani
what will take it from a 7

00:30:47.850 --> 00:30:50.530 align:middle line:84%
to a 10, he goes when you go
out of the country, Mommy,

00:30:50.530 --> 00:30:52.240 align:middle line:90%
I want to go with you.

00:30:52.240 --> 00:30:53.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:30:53.060 --> 00:30:54.604 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: The next
month, I took him

00:30:54.604 --> 00:30:55.770 align:middle line:90%
out of the school he was in.

00:30:55.770 --> 00:30:57.510 align:middle line:84%
I enrolled him in
a private school.

00:30:57.510 --> 00:31:00.110 align:middle line:84%
And the contingency of me
taking him to that school

00:31:00.110 --> 00:31:03.382 align:middle line:84%
was that when I
travel internationally

00:31:03.382 --> 00:31:04.840 align:middle line:84%
that he can distance
learn with me.

00:31:04.840 --> 00:31:05.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:31:05.220 --> 00:31:06.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: And he went
with me to Africa.

00:31:06.970 --> 00:31:08.355 align:middle line:84%
And then he went
with me to Kiev.

00:31:08.355 --> 00:31:10.310 align:middle line:90%
And he went with me to the--

00:31:10.310 --> 00:31:12.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's a better
education, by the way.

00:31:12.370 --> 00:31:14.292 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: And then
three years later, I

00:31:14.292 --> 00:31:15.500 align:middle line:90%
asked him the question again.

00:31:15.500 --> 00:31:17.480 align:middle line:84%
And he was like oh, it's
a nine, nine and a half.

00:31:17.480 --> 00:31:18.815 align:middle line:84%
And I said well, what will
take it from a nine and a half

00:31:18.815 --> 00:31:19.400 align:middle line:90%
to a ten?

00:31:19.400 --> 00:31:20.811 align:middle line:90%
He goes Mom--

00:31:20.811 --> 00:31:21.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's good.

00:31:21.560 --> 00:31:22.768 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: I don't even know.

00:31:22.768 --> 00:31:24.670 align:middle line:84%
It's just weird to say
it's a 10 with my Mom.

00:31:24.670 --> 00:31:26.180 align:middle line:84%
I'm like OK, it
goes to 9 and 1/2.

00:31:26.180 --> 00:31:28.555 align:middle line:84%
And then he said I don't need
to travel with you anymore.

00:31:28.555 --> 00:31:33.570 align:middle line:84%
So the movement in your
life happens in the action.

00:31:33.570 --> 00:31:37.340 align:middle line:84%
And that's also where the
butterflies or the birds

00:31:37.340 --> 00:31:38.770 align:middle line:90%
arise in your belly.

00:31:38.770 --> 00:31:40.680 align:middle line:84%
But that's also where
you get to push past

00:31:40.680 --> 00:31:41.850 align:middle line:90%
where you've stopped before.

00:31:41.850 --> 00:31:44.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What about agitation
when it happens at that moment

00:31:44.570 --> 00:31:47.700 align:middle line:84%
whereas maybe you hear something
you just don't want to change,

00:31:47.700 --> 00:31:50.540 align:middle line:84%
or want to hear, or
when you get frustrated,

00:31:50.540 --> 00:31:54.409 align:middle line:84%
when you hit that wall,
when you hit that breakdown?

00:31:54.409 --> 00:31:56.950 align:middle line:84%
And we talked about it earlier,
about going to that no matter

00:31:56.950 --> 00:31:58.126 align:middle line:90%
what place, right?

00:31:58.126 --> 00:31:58.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yes.

00:31:58.750 --> 00:32:00.083 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So it's going to happen.

00:32:00.083 --> 00:32:01.400 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yes, absolutely.

00:32:01.400 --> 00:32:03.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm not trying to
predict anything negative

00:32:03.260 --> 00:32:04.252 align:middle line:90%
in your future.

00:32:04.252 --> 00:32:05.710 align:middle line:84%
But as you will
have breakthroughs,

00:32:05.710 --> 00:32:06.751 align:middle line:90%
you will have breakdowns.

00:32:06.751 --> 00:32:07.480 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:32:07.480 --> 00:32:09.640 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're not
having breakdowns,

00:32:09.640 --> 00:32:10.960 align:middle line:90%
you're not playing big enough.

00:32:10.960 --> 00:32:11.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Gah.

00:32:11.470 --> 00:32:12.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: See,
your job is to keep

00:32:12.990 --> 00:32:15.710 align:middle line:84%
going to the edge
of your existence,

00:32:15.710 --> 00:32:18.960 align:middle line:84%
to the edge of your capacity,
to the edge of your knowing.

00:32:18.960 --> 00:32:22.140 align:middle line:84%
Your job is to keep yourself
right outside your comfort zone

00:32:22.140 --> 00:32:24.440 align:middle line:84%
for the sake of your
next big breakthrough.

00:32:24.440 --> 00:32:27.550 align:middle line:84%
And to play like this-- I'm
like this right now in my life.

00:32:27.550 --> 00:32:28.050 align:middle line:90%
I'm like--

00:32:28.050 --> 00:32:28.610 align:middle line:90%
[GASP]

00:32:28.610 --> 00:32:30.030 align:middle line:84%
--because so many
things are big.

00:32:30.030 --> 00:32:30.807 align:middle line:90%
They're ginormous.

00:32:30.807 --> 00:32:31.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:32:31.390 --> 00:32:33.800 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: So I'm not
necessarily comfortable,

00:32:33.800 --> 00:32:37.832 align:middle line:84%
but I'm uncomfortable inside the
excitement of what's possible.

00:32:37.832 --> 00:32:38.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ooo.

00:32:38.600 --> 00:32:39.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: So also
when you're there,

00:32:39.830 --> 00:32:41.746 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have
breakdowns because you're

00:32:41.746 --> 00:32:44.900 align:middle line:84%
going to find where your
limiting beliefs, Lisa, are

00:32:44.900 --> 00:32:45.750 align:middle line:90%
going to kick in.

00:32:45.750 --> 00:32:47.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you have
redefined your relationship

00:32:47.830 --> 00:32:48.960 align:middle line:90%
with breakdown.

00:32:48.960 --> 00:32:49.760 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: I have.

00:32:49.760 --> 00:32:50.580 align:middle line:90%
I have.

00:32:50.580 --> 00:32:51.413 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I hear that.

00:32:51.413 --> 00:32:52.420 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: I have.

00:32:52.420 --> 00:32:54.200 align:middle line:90%
Breakdown does not mean stop.

00:32:54.200 --> 00:32:55.787 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --not a bad thing.

00:32:55.787 --> 00:32:56.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: No.

00:32:56.370 --> 00:32:58.590 align:middle line:84%
Breakdown means
that I'm stretching,

00:32:58.590 --> 00:32:59.810 align:middle line:90%
my seams are screaming.

00:32:59.810 --> 00:33:01.300 align:middle line:84%
I call it my seams
are screaming.

00:33:01.300 --> 00:33:03.380 align:middle line:84%
You know like the seams
on the side of your jeans

00:33:03.380 --> 00:33:06.370 align:middle line:84%
when your jeans really
should not be on you anymore?

00:33:06.370 --> 00:33:09.920 align:middle line:84%
My seams are screaming because
I'm at the edge of what I know.

00:33:09.920 --> 00:33:11.410 align:middle line:84%
I'm at the edge
of what I've done.

00:33:11.410 --> 00:33:13.585 align:middle line:90%
I've outgrown this season.

00:33:13.585 --> 00:33:14.585 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's exciting.

00:33:14.585 --> 00:33:15.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Oh!

00:33:15.060 --> 00:33:16.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That could be exciting.

00:33:16.000 --> 00:33:17.958 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: If you look
at any area of your life

00:33:17.958 --> 00:33:20.470 align:middle line:84%
that rates a two or a
one inside the rating,

00:33:20.470 --> 00:33:22.090 align:middle line:84%
it could be that
you've completed

00:33:22.090 --> 00:33:23.700 align:middle line:84%
the season of it
looking like that.

00:33:23.700 --> 00:33:24.320 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Huh.

00:33:24.320 --> 00:33:26.680 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: See, when
I was motivating LA,

00:33:26.680 --> 00:33:28.554 align:middle line:84%
and I'm just in LA,
and all of a sudden,

00:33:28.554 --> 00:33:29.720 align:middle line:90%
I start feeling comfortable.

00:33:29.720 --> 00:33:32.385 align:middle line:84%
Like I feel limited, and I
feel-- I was in breakdown.

00:33:32.385 --> 00:33:33.760 align:middle line:84%
But I was in
breakdown because it

00:33:33.760 --> 00:33:35.390 align:middle line:90%
was time to motivate California.

00:33:35.390 --> 00:33:36.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my goodness.

00:33:36.390 --> 00:33:37.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: And then
around California, I

00:33:37.970 --> 00:33:38.940 align:middle line:90%
started having issues.

00:33:38.940 --> 00:33:40.675 align:middle line:84%
Then it was time to
do international.

00:33:40.675 --> 00:33:43.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now you started
off motivating teens.

00:33:43.530 --> 00:33:44.155 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yes.

00:33:44.155 --> 00:33:46.363 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I mean, not only
motivating, but listening to

00:33:46.363 --> 00:33:47.339 align:middle line:90%
and providing a forum.

00:33:47.339 --> 00:33:49.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Transformational
work for teens.

00:33:49.130 --> 00:33:49.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:33:49.510 --> 00:33:50.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yes.

00:33:50.090 --> 00:33:51.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's a
very clear distinction

00:33:51.340 --> 00:33:53.140 align:middle line:84%
that you have between
inspiration and transformation?

00:33:53.140 --> 00:33:54.515 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Very
clear distinction

00:33:54.515 --> 00:33:58.390 align:middle line:84%
between motivation,
information, inspiration,

00:33:58.390 --> 00:33:59.301 align:middle line:90%
and transformation.

00:33:59.301 --> 00:34:00.800 align:middle line:84%
Very clear distinction
between them.

00:34:00.800 --> 00:34:02.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What's the difference
real quick because I--

00:34:02.850 --> 00:34:04.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Information is
the delivery of content.

00:34:04.750 --> 00:34:07.249 align:middle line:84%
You do not have to be inspired,
it's the traffic school guy.

00:34:07.249 --> 00:34:08.622 align:middle line:90%
I don't care if you like me.

00:34:08.622 --> 00:34:11.080 align:middle line:84%
Get your pass after eight hours
of being in traffic school.

00:34:11.080 --> 00:34:11.530 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:34:11.530 --> 00:34:12.696 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: It's information.

00:34:12.696 --> 00:34:14.501 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately, a lot
of our teachers--

00:34:14.501 --> 00:34:16.750 align:middle line:84%
we have some great teachers
who inspire and motivate--

00:34:16.750 --> 00:34:19.291 align:middle line:84%
but a lot of teachers who are
just there for the information.

00:34:19.291 --> 00:34:20.940 align:middle line:84%
So you don't really
remember them.

00:34:20.940 --> 00:34:21.523 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:34:21.523 --> 00:34:23.602 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: So
that's information.

00:34:23.602 --> 00:34:24.560 align:middle line:90%
That's the first level.

00:34:24.560 --> 00:34:28.260 align:middle line:84%
The next is motivation, very
topical, excited, rah rah,

00:34:28.260 --> 00:34:29.570 align:middle line:90%
go go, run run!

00:34:29.570 --> 00:34:31.850 align:middle line:90%
You know, break the bricks.

00:34:31.850 --> 00:34:33.350 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Walk through
the fire, yeah.

00:34:33.350 --> 00:34:35.725 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Which is great
because that can jumpstart you.

00:34:35.725 --> 00:34:38.430 align:middle line:84%
And you need that to jumpstart
you, to get you kind of going.

00:34:38.430 --> 00:34:39.179 align:middle line:90%
But it's topical--

00:34:39.179 --> 00:34:40.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wakes you up.

00:34:40.070 --> 00:34:42.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: --it's topical, and
you need more in about 90 days.

00:34:42.730 --> 00:34:46.880 align:middle line:84%
And then inspiration is that
soul-stirring in your soul.

00:34:46.880 --> 00:34:48.179 align:middle line:90%
You get it kind of quiet.

00:34:48.179 --> 00:34:49.260 align:middle line:90%
It's not a loud thing.

00:34:49.260 --> 00:34:50.230 align:middle line:90%
It's a mmm.

00:34:50.230 --> 00:34:53.090 align:middle line:84%
You have a lot of
mmms with inspiration.

00:34:53.090 --> 00:34:56.880 align:middle line:84%
And it makes you want to be a
better woman, be a better man.

00:34:56.880 --> 00:35:00.002 align:middle line:84%
And then there's transformation,
the road less traveled.

00:35:00.002 --> 00:35:01.460 align:middle line:84%
That's when someone's
willing to go

00:35:01.460 --> 00:35:03.000 align:middle line:90%
with you to your darkest place--

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:03.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:35:03.660 --> 00:35:05.159 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: --and
walk out beside you

00:35:05.159 --> 00:35:07.012 align:middle line:90%
so you see a new possibility.

00:35:07.012 --> 00:35:09.220 align:middle line:84%
Every time I speak, I'm
talking about transformation,

00:35:09.220 --> 00:35:12.190 align:middle line:84%
which is why I say look
at these nine environments

00:35:12.190 --> 00:35:13.570 align:middle line:90%
in your life and rate them.

00:35:13.570 --> 00:35:14.587 align:middle line:90%
That's not fun.

00:35:14.587 --> 00:35:15.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:35:15.170 --> 00:35:16.870 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Go to the
relationship and ask them

00:35:16.870 --> 00:35:17.760 align:middle line:84%
how would you rate
this relationship?

00:35:17.760 --> 00:35:18.581 align:middle line:90%
That's not fun.

00:35:18.581 --> 00:35:19.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No.

00:35:19.080 --> 00:35:22.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: But on the other
side is a transformation.

00:35:22.980 --> 00:35:25.680 align:middle line:84%
On the other side
is something new

00:35:25.680 --> 00:35:28.650 align:middle line:90%
and potentially unrecognizable.

00:35:28.650 --> 00:35:30.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And does this
work with teenagers,

00:35:30.510 --> 00:35:34.610 align:middle line:84%
as well, who could be
talked to and at forever?

00:35:34.610 --> 00:35:37.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Lisa, I'm afraid
that those who are watching

00:35:37.460 --> 00:35:38.770 align:middle line:90%
won't even believe me.

00:35:38.770 --> 00:35:40.730 align:middle line:84%
They won't believe
what I've seen.

00:35:40.730 --> 00:35:45.850 align:middle line:84%
My company has worked with
over 210,000 teens worldwide.

00:35:45.850 --> 00:35:46.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:35:46.350 --> 00:35:52.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: 210,000 in
Montreal, and Quebec, and over

00:35:52.710 --> 00:35:58.460 align:middle line:84%
in Australia, and Switzerland
now, and Taipei, and in Africa.

00:35:58.460 --> 00:36:01.320 align:middle line:84%
And I could tell you
all over the world

00:36:01.320 --> 00:36:04.990 align:middle line:84%
and all 15-year-olds,
16-year-olds, 12-year-olds,

00:36:04.990 --> 00:36:09.190 align:middle line:84%
and 18-year-olds looking from
Africa, looking from Taipei,

00:36:09.190 --> 00:36:11.080 align:middle line:90%
and looking from Australia.

00:36:11.080 --> 00:36:13.420 align:middle line:84%
They all are ready
for transformation.

00:36:13.420 --> 00:36:14.481 align:middle line:90%
I kid you not.

00:36:14.481 --> 00:36:14.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Huh.

00:36:14.980 --> 00:36:16.979 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: They just want
it served on a platter

00:36:16.979 --> 00:36:18.080 align:middle line:90%
that they can understand.

00:36:18.080 --> 00:36:20.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you hear the
same thing from teens

00:36:20.800 --> 00:36:21.920 align:middle line:90%
all around the world?

00:36:21.920 --> 00:36:22.820 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: All around the world.

00:36:22.820 --> 00:36:23.611 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What is it?

00:36:23.611 --> 00:36:24.325 align:middle line:90%
What do you hear?

00:36:24.325 --> 00:36:27.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Oooh, are
you ready for it?

00:36:27.570 --> 00:36:29.286 align:middle line:90%
We don't listen.

00:36:29.286 --> 00:36:29.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Adults?

00:36:29.910 --> 00:36:31.035 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: We don't listen.

00:36:31.035 --> 00:36:32.690 align:middle line:90%
We don't listen to them.

00:36:32.690 --> 00:36:34.120 align:middle line:90%
We say what were you thinking?

00:36:34.120 --> 00:36:35.830 align:middle line:84%
And then before they
can discover it,

00:36:35.830 --> 00:36:37.420 align:middle line:90%
we give them their thoughts.

00:36:37.420 --> 00:36:38.112 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:36:38.112 --> 00:36:39.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: You
know, we've done it.

00:36:39.570 --> 00:36:43.400 align:middle line:84%
We don't let them speak
because the silence is

00:36:43.400 --> 00:36:45.510 align:middle line:90%
too awkward for us.

00:36:45.510 --> 00:36:46.510 align:middle line:90%
We don't let them speak.

00:36:46.510 --> 00:36:48.676 align:middle line:84%
And then if they don't say
what we want them to say,

00:36:48.676 --> 00:36:49.820 align:middle line:90%
then we go in on them.

00:36:49.820 --> 00:36:51.380 align:middle line:90%
So they're not safe.

00:36:51.380 --> 00:36:53.580 align:middle line:84%
They don't feel
emotionally safe.

00:36:53.580 --> 00:36:55.610 align:middle line:84%
It's hard to hear it,
but it's the truth,

00:36:55.610 --> 00:36:58.010 align:middle line:84%
which is why I will do this
work until the last breath

00:36:58.010 --> 00:36:59.870 align:middle line:90%
in my body leaves my soul.

00:36:59.870 --> 00:37:03.180 align:middle line:84%
Because what we do, we spend
an hour in our training,

00:37:03.180 --> 00:37:06.190 align:middle line:84%
an hour creating a safe
space so they really

00:37:06.190 --> 00:37:07.470 align:middle line:90%
get it's a save space.

00:37:07.470 --> 00:37:10.380 align:middle line:84%
And then once we do
that, flood gates.

00:37:10.380 --> 00:37:11.900 align:middle line:90%
But not just what's bad.

00:37:11.900 --> 00:37:14.800 align:middle line:84%
Flood gates are who they want
to be, the stuff they've done.

00:37:14.800 --> 00:37:19.160 align:middle line:84%
Parents are blown away when
they come to graduation,

00:37:19.160 --> 00:37:21.450 align:middle line:90%
and I say OK, talk to her now.

00:37:21.450 --> 00:37:24.650 align:middle line:84%
And a 17-year-old teenage
boy would say Mom,

00:37:24.650 --> 00:37:27.250 align:middle line:84%
so I'm sorry I broke the
integrity contract with you

00:37:27.250 --> 00:37:28.840 align:middle line:84%
when I told you
that I hated you.

00:37:28.840 --> 00:37:30.590 align:middle line:84%
And I apologize for
the way I treated you.

00:37:30.590 --> 00:37:32.180 align:middle line:84%
I know it must
have made you feel

00:37:32.180 --> 00:37:33.480 align:middle line:90%
unappreciated and unvalued.

00:37:33.480 --> 00:37:34.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I've got chills.

00:37:34.480 --> 00:37:36.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Here's what
I learned this weekend.

00:37:36.420 --> 00:37:39.730 align:middle line:84%
I learned that words don't
land on your on your ears, Mom.

00:37:39.730 --> 00:37:40.942 align:middle line:90%
They land on your heart.

00:37:40.942 --> 00:37:43.150 align:middle line:84%
And here's what I'm committed
to do differently, Mom.

00:37:43.150 --> 00:37:45.820 align:middle line:84%
I'm committed to press pause
on my negative self-talk

00:37:45.820 --> 00:37:48.820 align:middle line:84%
and play on my powerful
self-talk before I speak.

00:37:48.820 --> 00:37:52.260 align:middle line:84%
Parents are like this and
just sobbing, sobbing.

00:37:52.260 --> 00:37:52.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:37:52.920 --> 00:37:55.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: We have to
stand behind the parents

00:37:55.160 --> 00:37:57.100 align:middle line:90%
because they never thought that.

00:37:57.100 --> 00:37:59.410 align:middle line:84%
They brought their kids
there for us to fix them.

00:37:59.410 --> 00:38:00.630 align:middle line:84%
And the first thing
we say to their teens

00:38:00.630 --> 00:38:03.130 align:middle line:84%
is we're not going to fix you
because you are not broken.

00:38:03.130 --> 00:38:05.088 align:middle line:84%
We're just going to learn
how to listen to you,

00:38:05.088 --> 00:38:07.230 align:middle line:84%
and learn how to guide
you, and facilitate you

00:38:07.230 --> 00:38:09.210 align:middle line:90%
through the rough terrain.

00:38:09.210 --> 00:38:11.685 align:middle line:84%
It's the most
beautiful-- and I don't

00:38:11.685 --> 00:38:13.560 align:middle line:84%
say it's the most
beautiful terrain I've ever

00:38:13.560 --> 00:38:15.150 align:middle line:90%
seen because I created it.

00:38:15.150 --> 00:38:16.230 align:middle line:90%
I stand in it.

00:38:16.230 --> 00:38:17.920 align:middle line:90%
And I'm in awe.

00:38:17.920 --> 00:38:20.610 align:middle line:84%
I'm in awe of every
single time, Lisa.

00:38:20.610 --> 00:38:24.309 align:middle line:84%
210,000 teens, we have a
predictable transformation.

00:38:24.309 --> 00:38:25.100 align:middle line:90%
Every single time--

00:38:25.100 --> 00:38:26.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Every single time?

00:38:26.020 --> 00:38:27.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: --every single time
they get to the same result

00:38:27.980 --> 00:38:29.479 align:middle line:84%
no matter where we
are in the world.

00:38:29.479 --> 00:38:32.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What blows my mind is
that your son Jaylani is now--

00:38:32.020 --> 00:38:34.400 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: A facilitator.

00:38:34.400 --> 00:38:35.830 align:middle line:90%
He'll be 19 this year.

00:38:35.830 --> 00:38:37.140 align:middle line:90%
He now facilitates.

00:38:37.140 --> 00:38:39.820 align:middle line:84%
He facilitated
our last workshop,

00:38:39.820 --> 00:38:41.500 align:middle line:90%
and I just stopped talking.

00:38:41.500 --> 00:38:43.180 align:middle line:84%
Because we normally
co-facilitate.

00:38:43.180 --> 00:38:44.350 align:middle line:90%
I do about 70%.

00:38:44.350 --> 00:38:45.400 align:middle line:90%
He does about 30.

00:38:45.400 --> 00:38:48.130 align:middle line:84%
And I thought let me just stop
talking and see what happens.

00:38:48.130 --> 00:38:51.010 align:middle line:84%
And I stopped talking,
and he talked more.

00:38:51.010 --> 00:38:52.830 align:middle line:84%
I stopped a little
more, he'd talk more.

00:38:52.830 --> 00:38:53.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:38:53.330 --> 00:38:55.871 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: And then the room
got engaged in a different view.

00:38:55.871 --> 00:38:59.770 align:middle line:84%
I think I'm a good facilitator,
but I'm a 47-year-old woman.

00:38:59.770 --> 00:39:01.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:39:01.240 --> 00:39:04.016 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: He's a
18-year-old kid.

00:39:04.016 --> 00:39:04.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, he's--

00:39:04.890 --> 00:39:07.860 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: So it's a
now conversation now.

00:39:07.860 --> 00:39:11.050 align:middle line:84%
Man, so we're teaching
coming up soon.

00:39:11.050 --> 00:39:12.849 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to
do the same thing.

00:39:12.849 --> 00:39:13.640 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to quiet.

00:39:13.640 --> 00:39:14.015 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:39:14.015 --> 00:39:14.900 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: I'm going
to introduce him.

00:39:14.900 --> 00:39:17.067 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to relay with him
so he doesn't get stuck.

00:39:17.067 --> 00:39:18.650 align:middle line:84%
But it's the best
thing on the planet.

00:39:18.650 --> 00:39:19.540 align:middle line:90%
And he's not perfect.

00:39:19.540 --> 00:39:21.200 align:middle line:90%
And he shares his junk.

00:39:21.200 --> 00:39:22.840 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I braced
myself as a mother.

00:39:22.840 --> 00:39:23.600 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLE]

00:39:23.600 --> 00:39:25.220 align:middle line:84%
Because he knows
it's a safe space.

00:39:25.220 --> 00:39:27.710 align:middle line:84%
And he knows there are not
going to be any repercussions.

00:39:27.710 --> 00:39:28.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you have
to be the example.

00:39:28.910 --> 00:39:29.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: You have
to be the example.

00:39:29.960 --> 00:39:30.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:39:30.210 --> 00:39:32.168 align:middle line:84%
I have to show you this
video because it really

00:39:32.168 --> 00:39:34.720 align:middle line:84%
tells a lot about
motivating the teen spirit.

00:39:34.720 --> 00:39:36.222 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:39:36.222 --> 00:39:38.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Motivating the
Teen Spirit has been around

00:39:38.430 --> 00:39:40.030 align:middle line:90%
for a long, long time.

00:39:40.030 --> 00:39:42.450 align:middle line:84%
As of June of 2008
we've had the pleasure

00:39:42.450 --> 00:39:46.830 align:middle line:84%
of transforming lives
of over 210,000 teens.

00:39:46.830 --> 00:39:49.460 align:middle line:84%
We've had the pleasure of having
a track record where we've

00:39:49.460 --> 00:39:51.960 align:middle line:84%
prevented, on record
as of June of 2008,

00:39:51.960 --> 00:39:55.310 align:middle line:90%
over 3,053 teen suicides.

00:39:55.310 --> 00:39:57.340 align:middle line:84%
We are committed
to teaching teens

00:39:57.340 --> 00:39:59.380 align:middle line:84%
how to put words
to their feelings,

00:39:59.380 --> 00:40:01.740 align:middle line:84%
how to look at what's
going on on the inside,

00:40:01.740 --> 00:40:04.750 align:middle line:84%
and make sure it doesn't
cause a reaction or an action

00:40:04.750 --> 00:40:06.380 align:middle line:84%
that they're not
in alignment with,

00:40:06.380 --> 00:40:09.530 align:middle line:84%
a result that they can
manage and be proud of.

00:40:09.530 --> 00:40:13.400 align:middle line:84%
Motivating the Teen Spirit has
worked for years, since 2000,

00:40:13.400 --> 00:40:16.350 align:middle line:84%
teaching teens how to make
integrity-based decisions

00:40:16.350 --> 00:40:18.768 align:middle line:84%
and how to fall madly
in love with themselves.

00:40:18.768 --> 00:40:22.321 align:middle line:84%
>>I learned from my words that
I could really hurt somebody

00:40:22.321 --> 00:40:23.862 align:middle line:84%
because the day that
my brother died,

00:40:23.862 --> 00:40:26.107 align:middle line:84%
we had got in like
a big, big fight,

00:40:26.107 --> 00:40:28.440 align:middle line:84%
and we were fist-fighting
like all throughout the house.

00:40:28.440 --> 00:40:30.992 align:middle line:84%
And I was telling him like I
hate you, and I don't love you,

00:40:30.992 --> 00:40:31.950 align:middle line:90%
and you not my brother.

00:40:31.950 --> 00:40:33.533 align:middle line:84%
The first words that
come out my mouth

00:40:33.533 --> 00:40:36.880 align:middle line:84%
should be thought about
before I actually say them.

00:40:36.880 --> 00:40:38.380 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: We're
excited about where

00:40:38.380 --> 00:40:41.250 align:middle line:84%
we get to be because we believe
that with the skill sets

00:40:41.250 --> 00:40:43.920 align:middle line:84%
that we offer teens,
and we're considered

00:40:43.920 --> 00:40:48.200 align:middle line:84%
to be the top 1% in
self-development for teens.

00:40:48.200 --> 00:40:49.790 align:middle line:84%
>>One of my biggest
challenges that

00:40:49.790 --> 00:40:51.870 align:middle line:84%
Motivating the Teen
Spirit has helped me with

00:40:51.870 --> 00:40:56.420 align:middle line:84%
was actually talking about
the situation with my father.

00:40:56.420 --> 00:40:59.410 align:middle line:84%
With him being in jail, I was
kind of like, I didn't really

00:40:59.410 --> 00:41:01.710 align:middle line:84%
want to touch on that
subject because it brought up

00:41:01.710 --> 00:41:04.260 align:middle line:84%
too many feelings that I
didn't want to deal with.

00:41:04.260 --> 00:41:07.035 align:middle line:84%
And so talking about
him kind of like

00:41:07.035 --> 00:41:08.910 align:middle line:84%
helped me have a better
relationship with him

00:41:08.910 --> 00:41:11.605 align:middle line:84%
even though we don't see
each other that much.

00:41:11.605 --> 00:41:15.370 align:middle line:84%
And it helped me actually
realize that what he did

00:41:15.370 --> 00:41:18.570 align:middle line:84%
wasn't-- it wasn't his
choice to be away from me,

00:41:18.570 --> 00:41:20.080 align:middle line:84%
that it was something
that he did.

00:41:20.080 --> 00:41:23.054 align:middle line:84%
And he just had to
pay the price for it.

00:41:23.054 --> 00:41:24.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: We allow
teens and show teens

00:41:24.720 --> 00:41:26.520 align:middle line:84%
how to be a part of
their own breakthrough.

00:41:26.520 --> 00:41:27.570 align:middle line:90%
We work with parents.

00:41:27.570 --> 00:41:30.490 align:middle line:84%
It's an interactive
experiential learning program,

00:41:30.490 --> 00:41:32.780 align:middle line:84%
which means we're not
dictating all the time.

00:41:32.780 --> 00:41:34.120 align:middle line:90%
It's not a monologue.

00:41:34.120 --> 00:41:35.260 align:middle line:90%
It's a dialogue.

00:41:35.260 --> 00:41:38.095 align:middle line:84%
It's a conversation
between them and us.

00:41:38.095 --> 00:41:39.700 align:middle line:84%
And I believe no
one knows what's

00:41:39.700 --> 00:41:42.820 align:middle line:84%
going on in a young adult's
life better than they do.

00:41:42.820 --> 00:41:45.000 align:middle line:84%
And we give them a
safe space-- key word--

00:41:45.000 --> 00:41:49.080 align:middle line:84%
a safe space to identify
what's up for them.

00:41:49.080 --> 00:41:52.050 align:middle line:84%
How is their integrity in
alignment with their vision?

00:41:52.050 --> 00:41:54.560 align:middle line:84%
How do they put words
to a particular feeling?

00:41:54.560 --> 00:41:56.757 align:middle line:84%
How do they stop a
freight train from going

00:41:56.757 --> 00:41:58.340 align:middle line:84%
in the wrong direction
and turn around

00:41:58.340 --> 00:41:59.690 align:middle line:90%
and go in the right direction?

00:41:59.690 --> 00:42:00.950 align:middle line:90%
How do they find the voice?

00:42:00.950 --> 00:42:03.590 align:middle line:84%
How does that shy
teen find their voice?

00:42:03.590 --> 00:42:08.930 align:middle line:84%
>>I know it must have made
you feel really unhappy when

00:42:08.930 --> 00:42:12.500 align:middle line:84%
you saw your little girl
trying to commit suicide.

00:42:12.500 --> 00:42:15.585 align:middle line:84%
I learned that I
have more potential.

00:42:15.585 --> 00:42:19.090 align:middle line:84%
I learned that I'm
more confident.

00:42:19.090 --> 00:42:21.840 align:middle line:84%
I learned that I can be
more honest with myself now

00:42:21.840 --> 00:42:22.870 align:middle line:90%
from the way I feel.

00:42:22.870 --> 00:42:27.450 align:middle line:84%
I learned that you
guys do love me,

00:42:27.450 --> 00:42:30.300 align:middle line:84%
that you guys do care
about me, or else you

00:42:30.300 --> 00:42:32.534 align:middle line:84%
wouldn't be standing
here in front of me.

00:42:32.534 --> 00:42:34.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You said that
you felt that you were--

00:42:34.450 --> 00:42:36.630 align:middle line:84%
I thought that you
were born as a orator,

00:42:36.630 --> 00:42:40.230 align:middle line:84%
and that you have had past
lives speaking in Greek stages.

00:42:40.230 --> 00:42:43.090 align:middle line:84%
But you said you were
born to help teens.

00:42:43.090 --> 00:42:45.790 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: God put breath in my
body to transform teen lives.

00:42:45.790 --> 00:42:47.400 align:middle line:84%
I'm very clear on
my life assignment,

00:42:47.400 --> 00:42:50.430 align:middle line:84%
very clear on why
I'm here, very clear

00:42:50.430 --> 00:42:51.997 align:middle line:90%
of what I'm supposed to do.

00:42:51.997 --> 00:42:53.080 align:middle line:90%
Like that's my assignment.

00:42:53.080 --> 00:42:55.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you did that
before you had a teenager.

00:42:55.660 --> 00:42:56.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: I did.

00:42:56.840 --> 00:42:59.200 align:middle line:84%
You get your assignment when
you get your assignment.

00:42:59.200 --> 00:43:01.400 align:middle line:90%
I got it a long time ago.

00:43:01.400 --> 00:43:03.440 align:middle line:84%
When I had Jayloni
in my belly, I

00:43:03.440 --> 00:43:07.900 align:middle line:84%
was mentoring 62 little girls
in South Central Los Angeles off

00:43:07.900 --> 00:43:10.630 align:middle line:84%
of Normandy and Manchester
where the civil unrest was.

00:43:10.630 --> 00:43:11.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And you were how old?

00:43:11.930 --> 00:43:13.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: I was 26.

00:43:13.510 --> 00:43:14.940 align:middle line:90%
I was 26.

00:43:14.940 --> 00:43:18.250 align:middle line:84%
I started mentoring teenage
girls when I was 23.

00:43:18.250 --> 00:43:21.480 align:middle line:84%
And I created this program
when I was about 28.

00:43:21.480 --> 00:43:23.320 align:middle line:84%
And I've been doing
it ever sense.

00:43:23.320 --> 00:43:27.040 align:middle line:84%
And clear, clear that this is
why I was born, crystal clear.

00:43:27.040 --> 00:43:31.060 align:middle line:84%
And every time I do it,
every cell in my body

00:43:31.060 --> 00:43:33.430 align:middle line:84%
comes alive like I've
never seen before.

00:43:33.430 --> 00:43:34.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How do we get there?

00:43:34.790 --> 00:43:37.290 align:middle line:84%
How do we get there
to get in touch

00:43:37.290 --> 00:43:40.480 align:middle line:84%
that deeply with
our life's purpose?

00:43:40.480 --> 00:43:42.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Take your
head out the game first.

00:43:42.440 --> 00:43:44.760 align:middle line:84%
Quit thinking how can
I make money at it.

00:43:44.760 --> 00:43:46.850 align:middle line:84%
Quit thinking I need
to earn a living.

00:43:46.850 --> 00:43:48.350 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes your head
and your chatter

00:43:48.350 --> 00:43:52.430 align:middle line:84%
interrupts your purpose,
it interrupts your heart.

00:43:52.430 --> 00:43:56.220 align:middle line:84%
You're going to find your
sole purpose in your soul.

00:43:56.220 --> 00:43:58.060 align:middle line:84%
You're going to
find your soulness

00:43:58.060 --> 00:43:59.260 align:middle line:90%
in your gut and your belly.

00:43:59.260 --> 00:44:01.980 align:middle line:90%
It's between here and here.

00:44:01.980 --> 00:44:03.380 align:middle line:84%
That imaginary
baby in your belly

00:44:03.380 --> 00:44:05.010 align:middle line:90%
is going to jump when you do it.

00:44:05.010 --> 00:44:06.899 align:middle line:90%
And you've already done it.

00:44:06.899 --> 00:44:08.440 align:middle line:84%
You've already done
it so many times.

00:44:08.440 --> 00:44:12.170 align:middle line:84%
It's when you talk to kids,
or when you sit with elders,

00:44:12.170 --> 00:44:15.484 align:middle line:84%
or when you volunteer
somewhere, or when you--

00:44:15.484 --> 00:44:16.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It'll come up.

00:44:16.400 --> 00:44:18.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: --it'll show you at
some-- it'll just feel good.

00:44:18.450 --> 00:44:20.070 align:middle line:84%
The hair on the
back of your neck.

00:44:20.070 --> 00:44:21.570 align:middle line:84%
The hair on all
my head stands up.

00:44:21.570 --> 00:44:23.250 align:middle line:84%
But the hair on the
back of your neck--

00:44:23.250 --> 00:44:24.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You're constantly
inspired then, right?

00:44:24.810 --> 00:44:25.790 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: I am
greatly inspired.

00:44:25.790 --> 00:44:27.706 align:middle line:84%
You know, this started
at the back of my neck,

00:44:27.706 --> 00:44:29.370 align:middle line:90%
and it went all the way forward.

00:44:29.370 --> 00:44:30.725 align:middle line:90%
But you'll feel it.

00:44:30.725 --> 00:44:34.820 align:middle line:84%
And I tell people walk toward
that, walk toward that feeling.

00:44:34.820 --> 00:44:36.400 align:middle line:84%
Don't let your
head interrupt it.

00:44:36.400 --> 00:44:39.020 align:middle line:84%
It may not be what
you do for a fee.

00:44:39.020 --> 00:44:41.200 align:middle line:90%
It may be what you do for free.

00:44:41.200 --> 00:44:43.110 align:middle line:90%
I look at Dr. King.

00:44:43.110 --> 00:44:45.540 align:middle line:90%
Dr. King did it for free.

00:44:45.540 --> 00:44:47.800 align:middle line:90%
I look at Mahatma Gandhi.

00:44:47.800 --> 00:44:50.070 align:middle line:90%
Mahatma Gandhi did it for free.

00:44:50.070 --> 00:44:51.800 align:middle line:90%
I look at Mother Teresa.

00:44:51.800 --> 00:44:54.380 align:middle line:90%
She gave everything and did it.

00:44:54.380 --> 00:44:56.120 align:middle line:90%
I look at Nelson Mandela.

00:44:56.120 --> 00:45:01.580 align:middle line:84%
He did it 27 years with
no positive recognition.

00:45:01.580 --> 00:45:02.699 align:middle line:90%
So your life's purpose--

00:45:02.699 --> 00:45:04.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Actually,
a lot of adversity.

00:45:04.240 --> 00:45:05.150 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: A lot of adversity.

00:45:05.150 --> 00:45:05.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:45:05.880 --> 00:45:08.690 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: You know, so
your sole purpose normally

00:45:08.690 --> 00:45:12.370 align:middle line:84%
lives between the resume
and the job description.

00:45:12.370 --> 00:45:15.110 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't sit in any
one of those places.

00:45:15.110 --> 00:45:17.657 align:middle line:84%
It's your God assignment,
whatever you call your God.

00:45:17.657 --> 00:45:18.740 align:middle line:90%
It's your life assignment.

00:45:18.740 --> 00:45:19.830 align:middle line:90%
It's your breath assignment.

00:45:19.830 --> 00:45:20.913 align:middle line:90%
It may not be your resume.

00:45:20.913 --> 00:45:22.140 align:middle line:90%
And can you do both?

00:45:22.140 --> 00:45:22.839 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:45:22.839 --> 00:45:23.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:45:23.380 --> 00:45:25.296 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Yes, you may
need to earn a living.

00:45:25.296 --> 00:45:27.600 align:middle line:84%
And then you need to
live in your passion.

00:45:27.600 --> 00:45:30.410 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Mmm, and then what
happens is you wind up doing

00:45:30.410 --> 00:45:32.620 align:middle line:84%
both at the same time
because that's what--

00:45:32.620 --> 00:45:33.536 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Absolutely.

00:45:33.536 --> 00:45:35.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I volunteer at
the radio station still.

00:45:35.770 --> 00:45:36.686 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Absolutely.

00:45:36.686 --> 00:45:38.572 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: For 12 years
now, I do a radio show.

00:45:38.572 --> 00:45:39.780 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: That's how me met.

00:45:39.780 --> 00:45:40.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:45:40.140 --> 00:45:42.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: That's where we
first had our divine connection.

00:45:42.120 --> 00:45:42.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:45:42.600 --> 00:45:43.220 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Absolutely.

00:45:43.220 --> 00:45:45.000 align:middle line:84%
We wouldn't be here
if you weren't there.

00:45:45.000 --> 00:45:45.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:45:45.380 --> 00:45:46.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Look at where
your path leads you.

00:45:46.880 --> 00:45:48.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It was my hobby.

00:45:48.010 --> 00:45:49.310 align:middle line:90%
It was my passion.

00:45:49.310 --> 00:45:50.160 align:middle line:90%
It was the chance--

00:45:50.160 --> 00:45:50.785 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yes.

00:45:50.785 --> 00:45:53.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --my opportunity to
have a therapist session on air.

00:45:53.760 --> 00:45:55.710 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:45:55.710 --> 00:45:57.571 align:middle line:84%
And then 20,000
people listening,

00:45:57.571 --> 00:45:59.445 align:middle line:84%
but they were all having
the same experience.

00:45:59.445 --> 00:46:00.195 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Exactly

00:46:00.195 --> 00:46:01.449 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --because that's OK.

00:46:01.449 --> 00:46:02.240 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Exactly.

00:46:02.240 --> 00:46:04.920 align:middle line:90%
And you walk toward that.

00:46:04.920 --> 00:46:06.930 align:middle line:84%
You're here because
you said yes to that.

00:46:06.930 --> 00:46:07.895 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Many times.

00:46:07.895 --> 00:46:08.520 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yes.

00:46:08.520 --> 00:46:11.465 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And I paid for
it many times, you know,

00:46:11.465 --> 00:46:13.080 align:middle line:90%
out of my pocket for producers.

00:46:13.080 --> 00:46:13.705 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yes.

00:46:13.705 --> 00:46:16.035 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: But it was my destiny.

00:46:16.035 --> 00:46:16.660 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yes.

00:46:16.660 --> 00:46:17.909 align:middle line:90%
You were supposed to be there.

00:46:17.909 --> 00:46:18.590 align:middle line:90%
It fed you.

00:46:18.590 --> 00:46:19.532 align:middle line:90%
It pays you.

00:46:19.532 --> 00:46:22.100 align:middle line:84%
You know, people
look at my life.

00:46:22.100 --> 00:46:23.780 align:middle line:90%
And I have an amazing life.

00:46:23.780 --> 00:46:26.900 align:middle line:84%
And I'm blessed enough to
be a CEO of a multimillion

00:46:26.900 --> 00:46:28.440 align:middle line:84%
dollar company,
but they don't know

00:46:28.440 --> 00:46:30.510 align:middle line:90%
how many things I do for free.

00:46:30.510 --> 00:46:31.972 align:middle line:90%
I do so much for free.

00:46:31.972 --> 00:46:32.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, yeah.

00:46:32.680 --> 00:46:35.290 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: I do so much speaking
for free because I love it.

00:46:35.290 --> 00:46:36.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:46:36.000 --> 00:46:37.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Because
it's in my belly.

00:46:37.610 --> 00:46:40.920 align:middle line:84%
My baby in my belly
jumps when I do it.

00:46:40.920 --> 00:46:42.660 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to restrict it.

00:46:42.660 --> 00:46:44.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And now you
teach people to speak.

00:46:44.460 --> 00:46:45.500 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: I do.

00:46:45.500 --> 00:46:46.030 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:46:46.030 --> 00:46:46.945 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:46:46.945 --> 00:46:48.970 align:middle line:84%
You know, I've been
all around the world.

00:46:48.970 --> 00:46:50.050 align:middle line:90%
I have six best-sellers.

00:46:50.050 --> 00:46:53.590 align:middle line:84%
I've sat next to Larry
King, across from Oprah.

00:46:53.590 --> 00:46:56.084 align:middle line:84%
This wasn't even in
my dream early on.

00:46:56.084 --> 00:46:57.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Could you even know?

00:46:57.250 --> 00:46:58.880 align:middle line:90%
I doubt it.

00:46:58.880 --> 00:47:00.940 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Its so way beyond.

00:47:00.940 --> 00:47:02.028 align:middle line:90%
I got a fail in English.

00:47:02.028 --> 00:47:02.528 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:47:02.528 --> 00:47:03.611 align:middle line:90%
I've just got to tell you.

00:47:03.611 --> 00:47:06.720 align:middle line:84%
I got a fail in English and a
D minus in Speech, same year.

00:47:06.720 --> 00:47:10.140 align:middle line:84%
So when I got seven
figures to do the book that

00:47:10.140 --> 00:47:12.190 align:middle line:84%
had my face on the
cover-- you know,

00:47:12.190 --> 00:47:13.980 align:middle line:84%
I expected to do good
with "The Secret"

00:47:13.980 --> 00:47:15.470 align:middle line:84%
because there were so
many brilliant people.

00:47:15.470 --> 00:47:17.250 align:middle line:84%
You know, you can kind of hide
in between brilliant people.

00:47:17.250 --> 00:47:19.980 align:middle line:84%
And if it does well, you can go
it's because of him or because

00:47:19.980 --> 00:47:20.650 align:middle line:90%
of her.

00:47:20.650 --> 00:47:21.210 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:47:21.210 --> 00:47:22.910 align:middle line:84%
And then when I did
"Chicken Soup for the Soul,"

00:47:22.910 --> 00:47:24.786 align:middle line:84%
and it was so wildly
successful, I go well,

00:47:24.786 --> 00:47:26.160 align:middle line:84%
it's "Chicken Soup
for the Soul."

00:47:26.160 --> 00:47:27.243 align:middle line:90%
It's supposed to be great.

00:47:27.243 --> 00:47:30.430 align:middle line:84%
But when I did "No Matter What,"
and it was my chocolate face

00:47:30.430 --> 00:47:34.700 align:middle line:84%
on the cover and my
Afro, I was nervous.

00:47:34.700 --> 00:47:38.150 align:middle line:84%
But when someone gave me
seven figures for that book,

00:47:38.150 --> 00:47:40.330 align:middle line:90%
they said we love you.

00:47:40.330 --> 00:47:41.330 align:middle line:90%
That was what that said.

00:47:41.330 --> 00:47:42.871 align:middle line:84%
We love you, and we
adore you, and we

00:47:42.871 --> 00:47:45.260 align:middle line:84%
want to share you
with the world.

00:47:45.260 --> 00:47:47.260 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know what else
to dream for after that.

00:47:47.260 --> 00:47:48.410 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's just who
you are though, Lisa.

00:47:48.410 --> 00:47:48.994 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it is.

00:47:48.994 --> 00:47:50.993 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: I didn't know
what else to dream for.

00:47:50.993 --> 00:47:51.890 align:middle line:90%
So I prayed to God.

00:47:51.890 --> 00:47:53.681 align:middle line:84%
God, what should I be
doing in this season?

00:47:53.681 --> 00:47:56.170 align:middle line:84%
And what came back to
me was teach others.

00:47:56.170 --> 00:47:58.300 align:middle line:84%
Teach others how
to build a brand,

00:47:58.300 --> 00:48:02.990 align:middle line:84%
how to build a international
message, how to serve millions,

00:48:02.990 --> 00:48:05.600 align:middle line:84%
how to touch people
on multiple platforms,

00:48:05.600 --> 00:48:11.520 align:middle line:84%
books, CDs, voice, stage,
live, video, show them.

00:48:11.520 --> 00:48:13.560 align:middle line:84%
So I said OK because
that's what I do.

00:48:13.560 --> 00:48:14.630 align:middle line:90%
I'm obedient.

00:48:14.630 --> 00:48:16.950 align:middle line:84%
So this whole
season I'm committed

00:48:16.950 --> 00:48:19.200 align:middle line:84%
to taking brilliant
minds like you who

00:48:19.200 --> 00:48:21.380 align:middle line:84%
may have just set on
the radio and put you

00:48:21.380 --> 00:48:24.080 align:middle line:84%
on stage in front of several
hundred hungry people.

00:48:24.080 --> 00:48:24.927 align:middle line:90%
I did that.

00:48:24.927 --> 00:48:25.885 align:middle line:90%
We did that a year ago.

00:48:25.885 --> 00:48:26.509 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --ever.

00:48:26.509 --> 00:48:27.840 align:middle line:90%
I had never been on stage.

00:48:27.840 --> 00:48:31.150 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't stand
it for a second.

00:48:31.150 --> 00:48:32.010 align:middle line:90%
And then you did it.

00:48:32.010 --> 00:48:34.680 align:middle line:84%
You said get up there
and show your greatness.

00:48:34.680 --> 00:48:37.400 align:middle line:84%
And your audience
is so gracious.

00:48:37.400 --> 00:48:40.940 align:middle line:84%
They're so beautiful the
way that they just received.

00:48:40.940 --> 00:48:43.930 align:middle line:84%
And all of my self-chatter was
not going on in their heads.

00:48:43.930 --> 00:48:46.020 align:middle line:84%
And they made that appeared
apparent very fast.

00:48:46.020 --> 00:48:48.270 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: That's the season
I'm in is to teach people

00:48:48.270 --> 00:48:50.510 align:middle line:84%
how to get their divine
message out to the world.

00:48:50.510 --> 00:48:51.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That was beautiful.

00:48:51.340 --> 00:48:51.840 align:middle line:90%
That was beautiful.

00:48:51.840 --> 00:48:53.381 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Thank
you for trusting me.

00:48:53.381 --> 00:48:55.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, God,
when you told me

00:48:55.330 --> 00:48:57.745 align:middle line:84%
that you trusted me
to do that, I remember

00:48:57.745 --> 00:48:58.870 align:middle line:90%
sitting in the parking lot.

00:48:58.870 --> 00:49:00.270 align:middle line:84%
I was sitting and just
tears streaming down

00:49:00.270 --> 00:49:01.750 align:middle line:90%
my face like she believes in me.

00:49:01.750 --> 00:49:03.055 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: I do.

00:49:03.055 --> 00:49:05.305 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You have these
messages that are so inspiring.

00:49:05.305 --> 00:49:07.800 align:middle line:84%
And you really could
motivate a salt shaker.

00:49:07.800 --> 00:49:08.664 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:49:08.664 --> 00:49:10.330 align:middle line:84%
Like it would jump
up and become pepper.

00:49:10.330 --> 00:49:12.514 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Right, right.

00:49:12.514 --> 00:49:13.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What would
you tell people

00:49:13.930 --> 00:49:18.070 align:middle line:84%
who have had and will
have in the future tragedy

00:49:18.070 --> 00:49:20.040 align:middle line:84%
that's happened
in our home town,

00:49:20.040 --> 00:49:24.920 align:middle line:84%
in Newtown, in Boston, in New
York, and wherever it has?

00:49:24.920 --> 00:49:29.840 align:middle line:84%
How do you express your
greatness into them

00:49:29.840 --> 00:49:31.914 align:middle line:90%
when they have massive loss?

00:49:31.914 --> 00:49:33.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: May I look
right at them and speak?

00:49:33.830 --> 00:49:34.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:49:34.430 --> 00:49:36.429 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: So what I would
say to anyone, to you

00:49:36.429 --> 00:49:39.270 align:middle line:84%
if you've experienced
any type of breakdown,

00:49:39.270 --> 00:49:43.265 align:middle line:84%
emotional, spiritual,
financial, physical

00:49:43.265 --> 00:49:48.990 align:middle line:84%
is to always remember that the
human spirit is unbreakable.

00:49:48.990 --> 00:49:52.900 align:middle line:84%
Your human spirit is
untouchable, it's unstoppable.

00:49:52.900 --> 00:49:56.910 align:middle line:84%
Your human spirit isn't
even available to a tragedy.

00:49:56.910 --> 00:49:58.920 align:middle line:84%
Your body, your emotions
can be impacted,

00:49:58.920 --> 00:50:02.500 align:middle line:84%
but your human spirit
will always stay intact.

00:50:02.500 --> 00:50:06.510 align:middle line:84%
And if you can feel the
ground, then you can get up.

00:50:06.510 --> 00:50:09.380 align:middle line:84%
If you can feel, if you
have life in your body,

00:50:09.380 --> 00:50:13.430 align:middle line:84%
then it's your birthright
not just to turn your crawl

00:50:13.430 --> 00:50:16.510 align:middle line:84%
into a walk, your
walk into a run,

00:50:16.510 --> 00:50:19.380 align:middle line:84%
but to turn your
run into a soar.

00:50:19.380 --> 00:50:21.190 align:middle line:90%
That's your birthright.

00:50:21.190 --> 00:50:23.390 align:middle line:84%
Simply because you have
breath in your body,

00:50:23.390 --> 00:50:26.500 align:middle line:84%
and you can hear my voice,
that's your birthright.

00:50:26.500 --> 00:50:31.200 align:middle line:84%
And don't you dare let a bomber,
a shooter, or anyone else

00:50:31.200 --> 00:50:33.330 align:middle line:90%
take that right from you.

00:50:33.330 --> 00:50:35.390 align:middle line:90%
Show them what you're made of.

00:50:35.390 --> 00:50:39.220 align:middle line:84%
In the most positive,
conscious, aware, loving space,

00:50:39.220 --> 00:50:43.310 align:middle line:84%
love truly can bring
brightness to any dark corner.

00:50:43.310 --> 00:50:45.810 align:middle line:84%
And you just remember
that in this moment

00:50:45.810 --> 00:50:49.080 align:middle line:84%
I said if you lack
faith, borrow mine

00:50:49.080 --> 00:50:50.260 align:middle line:90%
because I have faith in you.

00:50:50.260 --> 00:50:51.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:50:51.580 --> 00:50:56.245 align:middle line:84%
I see you with a captain's
jacket and the stripes

00:50:56.245 --> 00:50:58.130 align:middle line:90%
on it saying I got up.

00:50:58.130 --> 00:50:58.820 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yes.

00:50:58.820 --> 00:50:59.870 align:middle line:90%
I got up.

00:50:59.870 --> 00:51:00.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I got up.

00:51:00.930 --> 00:51:04.060 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: I got up from
this, and this, and this,

00:51:04.060 --> 00:51:06.050 align:middle line:90%
and there's nothing to hide.

00:51:06.050 --> 00:51:09.380 align:middle line:84%
See, when you stop wondering
if you have to hide it,

00:51:09.380 --> 00:51:13.390 align:middle line:84%
and If you have to defend
it-- my grandmother says baby,

00:51:13.390 --> 00:51:17.110 align:middle line:84%
there's nothing to hide, nothing
to defend, nothing to protect,

00:51:17.110 --> 00:51:18.380 align:middle line:90%
and nothing to prove.

00:51:18.380 --> 00:51:19.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:51:19.120 --> 00:51:22.010 align:middle line:84%
Is there anything that you
would change looking back?

00:51:22.010 --> 00:51:24.100 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: On my journey?

00:51:24.100 --> 00:51:26.751 align:middle line:84%
Mmm, I'd keep working
out after college.

00:51:26.751 --> 00:51:28.790 align:middle line:84%
I'd work out a little
more consistently.

00:51:28.790 --> 00:51:34.280 align:middle line:84%
I never knew these knees could
feel this way in the morning.

00:51:34.280 --> 00:51:34.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:51:34.860 --> 00:51:37.469 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: I would have
taken off the gloves.

00:51:37.469 --> 00:51:38.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What do you mean?

00:51:38.510 --> 00:51:40.051 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: I would
have not beat Lisa

00:51:40.051 --> 00:51:42.800 align:middle line:90%
up so much in my early years.

00:51:42.800 --> 00:51:45.620 align:middle line:84%
I would've loved me
more to get here.

00:51:45.620 --> 00:51:49.130 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't have
judged me so much.

00:51:49.130 --> 00:51:53.190 align:middle line:84%
I would've stretched to see
myself through the lenses

00:51:53.190 --> 00:51:55.692 align:middle line:84%
that you see me through,
versus the lenses

00:51:55.692 --> 00:51:57.150 align:middle line:84%
that I was looking
at Lisa through.

00:51:57.150 --> 00:51:59.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Could you
have done that then?

00:51:59.260 --> 00:52:01.050 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: I don't know.

00:52:01.050 --> 00:52:05.095 align:middle line:84%
I always say I wish if I were
ever 20 again that I'd still

00:52:05.095 --> 00:52:07.180 align:middle line:90%
get to know what I know at 47.

00:52:07.180 --> 00:52:09.610 align:middle line:84%
See, I don't want to be 20
and just know what 20 knows.

00:52:09.610 --> 00:52:10.193 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:52:10.193 --> 00:52:12.913 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: I want to know what
I know now and just be perky--

00:52:12.913 --> 00:52:14.360 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:52:14.360 --> 00:52:17.351 align:middle line:90%
--like I was at 27.

00:52:17.351 --> 00:52:17.850 align:middle line:90%
I'm a girl.

00:52:17.850 --> 00:52:18.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's real.

00:52:18.180 --> 00:52:19.422 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: You
know, I'm just real.

00:52:19.422 --> 00:52:20.250 align:middle line:90%
Keeping it real.

00:52:20.250 --> 00:52:20.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Keeping it real.

00:52:20.790 --> 00:52:21.915 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Keeping it real.

00:52:21.915 --> 00:52:29.880 align:middle line:84%
And so I think if I had
anything to do differently-- I

00:52:29.880 --> 00:52:35.560 align:middle line:84%
appreciate all my battle wounds
because the battle wound is

00:52:35.560 --> 00:52:40.310 align:middle line:84%
a part of my victory v. My
battle wound is only half

00:52:40.310 --> 00:52:41.700 align:middle line:90%
of my victory v.

00:52:41.700 --> 00:52:42.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:52:42.200 --> 00:52:43.920 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: And I can't
have my victory v

00:52:43.920 --> 00:52:46.220 align:middle line:90%
without that experience.

00:52:46.220 --> 00:52:50.170 align:middle line:84%
I am the woman I am
today because I got up

00:52:50.170 --> 00:52:53.706 align:middle line:90%
from this, and this, and this.

00:52:53.706 --> 00:52:56.350 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't be the same
woman sitting here.

00:52:56.350 --> 00:53:01.240 align:middle line:84%
So I don't apologize
for being abused

00:53:01.240 --> 00:53:03.070 align:middle line:90%
emotionally and physically.

00:53:03.070 --> 00:53:05.740 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sorry that I had to
get on government's assistance

00:53:05.740 --> 00:53:07.715 align:middle line:90%
and stand in the WIC line.

00:53:07.715 --> 00:53:09.810 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sorry that I
didn't have Pampers

00:53:09.810 --> 00:53:13.240 align:middle line:84%
to put on my son or
food to feed him.

00:53:13.240 --> 00:53:16.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm not upset that I got
failed in English and in Speech

00:53:16.340 --> 00:53:18.485 align:middle line:84%
and was told I should
never write or speak.

00:53:18.485 --> 00:53:20.440 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You don't say,
at any moment, God,

00:53:20.440 --> 00:53:21.340 align:middle line:90%
I wish it wouldn't--

00:53:21.340 --> 00:53:23.320 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: No, not at all.

00:53:23.320 --> 00:53:28.320 align:middle line:84%
because there's some
part of my flame,

00:53:28.320 --> 00:53:32.420 align:middle line:84%
that was the log that had
to be put in the fire.

00:53:32.420 --> 00:53:34.665 align:middle line:90%
I wouldn't be who I am today.

00:53:34.665 --> 00:53:37.920 align:middle line:84%
And in order to love
who you are today,

00:53:37.920 --> 00:53:41.130 align:middle line:84%
you have to embrace
every single part.

00:53:41.130 --> 00:53:46.710 align:middle line:84%
The goodbyes that I didn't
want to give to my grandmother,

00:53:46.710 --> 00:53:48.460 align:middle line:90%
to the people that I love.

00:53:48.460 --> 00:53:50.244 align:middle line:90%
Something in me had to rise.

00:53:50.244 --> 00:53:51.660 align:middle line:84%
Here's what you
have to understand

00:53:51.660 --> 00:53:53.310 align:middle line:90%
about a breakthrough.

00:53:53.310 --> 00:53:56.020 align:middle line:84%
Something in you has to
rise that didn't even

00:53:56.020 --> 00:53:59.280 align:middle line:84%
exist before to get from
breakdown to breakthrough.

00:53:59.280 --> 00:54:00.820 align:middle line:90%
You have to hear that, Lisa.

00:54:00.820 --> 00:54:03.136 align:middle line:84%
If you go through
something right now,

00:54:03.136 --> 00:54:05.510 align:middle line:84%
you can't get through it if
you've never gone through it.

00:54:05.510 --> 00:54:07.790 align:middle line:84%
Again, you can't get
through it without something

00:54:07.790 --> 00:54:10.890 align:middle line:84%
from your character,
perseverance, determination,

00:54:10.890 --> 00:54:14.620 align:middle line:84%
forgiveness that you didn't
know you had it to that depth,

00:54:14.620 --> 00:54:17.350 align:middle line:90%
rising to a higher level.

00:54:17.350 --> 00:54:21.900 align:middle line:84%
See, your breakdowns
and your breakthroughs

00:54:21.900 --> 00:54:25.290 align:middle line:84%
help to form who
you're becoming.

00:54:25.290 --> 00:54:28.300 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: See, that's the thing is
it's somewhere in between then,

00:54:28.300 --> 00:54:29.280 align:middle line:90%
people get numb.

00:54:29.280 --> 00:54:30.542 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Yes.

00:54:30.542 --> 00:54:32.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And they
lose this passion.

00:54:32.000 --> 00:54:34.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Yeah, they say
I can't do it, but you can.

00:54:34.670 --> 00:54:37.150 align:middle line:90%
What would you do?

00:54:37.150 --> 00:54:39.420 align:middle line:84%
How would you
operate if you got up

00:54:39.420 --> 00:54:42.160 align:middle line:90%
every day knowing you would win?

00:54:42.160 --> 00:54:45.260 align:middle line:84%
You might run to your
victory, soar to your victory,

00:54:45.260 --> 00:54:46.330 align:middle line:90%
or crawl to your victory.

00:54:46.330 --> 00:54:50.500 align:middle line:84%
But if you knew the victory was
yours, how would you operate?

00:54:50.500 --> 00:54:54.140 align:middle line:84%
See, we live like
we're still questioning

00:54:54.140 --> 00:54:55.780 align:middle line:84%
if we're going to
have a victory.

00:54:55.780 --> 00:54:56.655 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, right.

00:54:56.655 --> 00:55:00.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: See, unwavering
faith, unwavering faith,

00:55:00.590 --> 00:55:02.114 align:middle line:90%
unwavering faith--

00:55:02.114 --> 00:55:03.780 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, we don't
wake up that way.

00:55:03.780 --> 00:55:04.320 align:middle line:90%
I don't wake up that way.

00:55:04.320 --> 00:55:05.486 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Unwavering faith.

00:55:05.486 --> 00:55:07.450 align:middle line:84%
But see, you get to
move your mental zip

00:55:07.450 --> 00:55:10.180 align:middle line:90%
code to unwavering faith.

00:55:10.180 --> 00:55:13.450 align:middle line:84%
See, I don't ever wonder
if I'm going to make it.

00:55:13.450 --> 00:55:16.025 align:middle line:84%
I just wonder what my
route today will be.

00:55:16.025 --> 00:55:17.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you ever
just be, though,

00:55:17.900 --> 00:55:21.790 align:middle line:84%
in that-- because I find
that over-achiever muscle is

00:55:21.790 --> 00:55:24.210 align:middle line:90%
over-worked and super-developed.

00:55:24.210 --> 00:55:27.670 align:middle line:84%
And it needs to
feel and be more.

00:55:27.670 --> 00:55:28.930 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Be more what?

00:55:28.930 --> 00:55:30.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Just in the moment.

00:55:30.110 --> 00:55:31.526 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: What
does it look like?

00:55:31.526 --> 00:55:32.450 align:middle line:90%
Define it.

00:55:32.450 --> 00:55:34.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That moment, or
what I'm talking about?

00:55:34.450 --> 00:55:36.840 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: Define it so
you can give yourself it.

00:55:36.840 --> 00:55:39.920 align:middle line:84%
See, as long as it sits in the
slightest bit of ambiguity,

00:55:39.920 --> 00:55:42.040 align:middle line:90%
it's always going to elude you.

00:55:42.040 --> 00:55:42.860 align:middle line:90%
I need to be more.

00:55:42.860 --> 00:55:44.680 align:middle line:90%
Be more what in this moment?

00:55:44.680 --> 00:55:45.532 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Just still.

00:55:45.532 --> 00:55:46.740 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: OK, then be still.

00:55:46.740 --> 00:55:49.780 align:middle line:90%
Then can you be enough?

00:55:49.780 --> 00:55:51.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a good question.

00:55:51.830 --> 00:55:52.890 align:middle line:90%
That is a good question.

00:55:52.890 --> 00:55:53.230 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: Right.

00:55:53.230 --> 00:55:53.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I don't think so.

00:55:53.910 --> 00:55:55.690 align:middle line:84%
I think stillness
means empty to me.

00:55:55.690 --> 00:55:59.310 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: So then
movement means proving.

00:55:59.310 --> 00:56:00.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:56:00.120 --> 00:56:01.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: See, I--
we can keep going.

00:56:01.710 --> 00:56:02.970 align:middle line:90%
We'll find the core.

00:56:02.970 --> 00:56:04.570 align:middle line:90%
Movement means proving.

00:56:04.570 --> 00:56:06.690 align:middle line:84%
So then I would ask
you the question,

00:56:06.690 --> 00:56:09.895 align:middle line:84%
who are you proving
it to and why?

00:56:09.895 --> 00:56:11.985 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to say
guarantee, but I can almost

00:56:11.985 --> 00:56:13.580 align:middle line:90%
guarantee you this, Lisa.

00:56:13.580 --> 00:56:16.110 align:middle line:84%
You're proving to something
that you've already

00:56:16.110 --> 00:56:18.290 align:middle line:84%
outlived, something
you've already done.

00:56:18.290 --> 00:56:21.760 align:middle line:84%
It's an old conversation
that you had as a child

00:56:21.760 --> 00:56:24.340 align:middle line:84%
or as a teenager that was
brought on by a mother,

00:56:24.340 --> 00:56:27.870 align:middle line:84%
by a father, by a boyfriend,
by someone early on.

00:56:27.870 --> 00:56:29.255 align:middle line:90%
And it kicked you in overdrive.

00:56:29.255 --> 00:56:32.740 align:middle line:90%
And you said never again.

00:56:32.740 --> 00:56:36.660 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to tell you
what a gentleman told me.

00:56:36.660 --> 00:56:40.804 align:middle line:90%
1999 or 2000, I got an award.

00:56:40.804 --> 00:56:42.262 align:middle line:84%
And when I got up
to get the award,

00:56:42.262 --> 00:56:46.290 align:middle line:84%
it was a very conscious
community in meditation,

00:56:46.290 --> 00:56:47.880 align:middle line:90%
much like this community.

00:56:47.880 --> 00:56:49.380 align:middle line:84%
And I got up to get
the award, and I

00:56:49.380 --> 00:56:53.100 align:middle line:84%
was like I'm going to make
it, with you or without you.

00:56:53.100 --> 00:56:54.940 align:middle line:90%
It was a total misfit.

00:56:54.940 --> 00:56:58.740 align:middle line:84%
And this generous man
pulled me to the back.

00:56:58.740 --> 00:57:00.340 align:middle line:84%
He was the one who
gave me the award.

00:57:00.340 --> 00:57:03.510 align:middle line:84%
And he goes you had to fight
to get out of South Central.

00:57:03.510 --> 00:57:04.810 align:middle line:90%
I said I sure did.

00:57:04.810 --> 00:57:06.410 align:middle line:84%
And you had to
prove it to people.

00:57:06.410 --> 00:57:08.050 align:middle line:90%
I said I sure did.

00:57:08.050 --> 00:57:10.800 align:middle line:90%
He said and you did.

00:57:10.800 --> 00:57:13.350 align:middle line:84%
And now you need to tell
yourself you already proved it.

00:57:13.350 --> 00:57:14.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, wow.

00:57:14.160 --> 00:57:16.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: So I tell you
you've already proven it.

00:57:16.620 --> 00:57:19.050 align:middle line:84%
And if we dig deeper
on another time,

00:57:19.050 --> 00:57:20.780 align:middle line:90%
we'll know what that thing is.

00:57:20.780 --> 00:57:23.400 align:middle line:84%
And then you'll realize
oh, I already proved it.

00:57:23.400 --> 00:57:24.400 align:middle line:90%
I forgot to tell myself.

00:57:24.400 --> 00:57:27.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I forgot-- I
forgot to tell myself.

00:57:27.260 --> 00:57:30.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: I've been so busy
being busy, being busy, being

00:57:30.980 --> 00:57:35.000 align:middle line:84%
busy that I forgot to tell
myself that I'm enough.

00:57:35.000 --> 00:57:36.710 align:middle line:90%
Now I'm enough.

00:57:36.710 --> 00:57:41.052 align:middle line:84%
I didn't think I was
then, but now I'm enough.

00:57:41.052 --> 00:57:44.390 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I have lost
track of all time.

00:57:44.390 --> 00:57:48.510 align:middle line:84%
I know that we are
wrapping it up here.

00:57:48.510 --> 00:57:55.430 align:middle line:84%
And I just invite listeners
with what exactly you just said.

00:57:55.430 --> 00:57:56.340 align:middle line:90%
You are enough.

00:57:56.340 --> 00:57:59.082 align:middle line:90%


00:57:59.082 --> 00:58:00.000 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:58:00.000 --> 00:58:01.083 align:middle line:90%
>>NICHOLS: You're welcome.

00:58:01.083 --> 00:58:02.356 align:middle line:90%
My pleasure.

00:58:02.356 --> 00:58:04.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This pleasure's
always mine with you.

00:58:04.660 --> 00:58:06.035 align:middle line:84%
>>NICHOLS: My
pleasure, we share.

00:58:06.035 --> 00:58:06.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Thanks, Lis.

